                    <sense xml:id="Tmain" xml:lang="en" source="#traces"> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><quote> sarḥat </quote></cit>, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ርስሐት</foreign> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><quote> rəsḥat </quote></cit> <pos expand="Substantivum">subst.</pos> <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><quote> sending back </quote></cit>, <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><quote> freeing </quote></cit>, <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><quote> release </quote></cit> <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወሶበ፡ ኮነ፡ ሰርሐተ፡ ሕዝብ፡ ወሖረ፡ አባ፡ ሙሴ፡ ከመ፡ ይትባረክ፡ እመቃብረ፡ ቅዱሳን።</foreign> ‘<cit type="translation" xml:lang="fr"><quote> Quand les gens furent renvoyés, abbā Musē alla recevoir la bénédiction du tombeau des saints </quote></cit>’ <bibl><ptr target="bm:Colin1986Maskaram"/><citedRange unit="page"> 28 (346) l. 29-30 (ed.); 29 (347) l. 30-31 (tr.)</citedRange></bibl> (‘Le mot <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሰርሐት፡</foreign>, inconnu des dictionnaires, doit être un substantif formé sur le verbe arabe <foreign xml:lang="ar">سرح</foreign> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><quote>saraḥa</quote></cit> «renvoyer, libérer».’ <bibl><ptr target="bm:Colin1986Maskaram"/><citedRange unit="page"> 29 (347) n. 9</citedRange></bibl>) <nd/> </sense>
